
[1]pathology

   PATHOL'OGY, n. [Gr. passion, suffering, and discourse.] That part of
   medicine which explains the nature of diseases, their causes and
   symptoms; or the doctrine of the causes and nature of diseases,
   comprehending nosology, etiology, symptomatology, and therapeutics.
